Hello
I am 30 years old.
I started drinking Coke at 20 years old,
I have never taken every day, I was not very addicted
I took it one or two times a month at most, But for about six months to a year now, I have been unable to control myself when I drink alcohol.
Even if before I promised myself not to go look for some coke, after two or three drinks I start to feel hot and I tell myself "let's go, we only have one life, it's party time", and it's impossible for me to control myself too much desire to take some.
So I know the problem is alcohol at the base but it's crazy, it's impossible to stop in family among friends for the aperitif etc.
Does someone have this problem?
Thank you
Stop drinking and the problem will be solved
One must sometimes force oneself to stop ...
Have you at least talked to your family doctor about it?
Seeing an addict could be beneficial for you, especially for "evaluating" your consumption
In fact, it's at night that it's harder to maintain mental level
The day is going well
Hello,
I am a political alcoholic.
I have been sober from alcohol for several years, but I can't seem to tell myself that I won't drink a drop of alcohol, even though I want to, perhaps not enough willpower.
I often find myself getting carried away on occasions because it's stronger than me and as soon as I start, it's impossible for me to stop,
After I sleep poorly and am sick the next day, and especially I hate myself,
I am ashamed, of who I become when I drink and I suffer from it,
I can't drink normally.
I drink all my dry glasses,
Why do I have this relationship with alcohol when so many people can drink normally?
I haven't drunk for ten days,
This weekend I am invited to an anniversary and I am very very afraid,
If you understand me, live the same thing or have passed the threshold, I take whatever can help me.
Thank you for reading me and I await your responses.
